p(x) = \sum_{j=0}^{6} \frac{1}{2^j} \prod_{\substack{0 \leq m \leq 6 \\ m \neq j}} \frac{x - 2^m}{2^j - 2^m}
\] <answer>Now let's calculate the value of $p(0)$ using the polynomial $p(x)$ we just derived. \[
p(0) = \sum_{j=0}^{6} \frac{1}{2^j} \prod_{\substack{0 \leq m \leq 6 \\ m \neq j}} \frac{-2^m}{2^j - 2^m} = \sum_{j=0}^{6} \frac{1}{2^j} \prod_{\substack{0 \leq m \leq 6 \\ m \neq j}} \frac{-1}{1 - 2^{m-j}}
\] \[
p(0) = \sum_{j=0}^{6} \frac{(-1)^{6-j}}{2^j} \prod_{\substack{0 \leq m \leq 6 \\ m \neq j}} \frac{1}{1 - 2^{m-j}} = \sum_{j=0}^{6} \frac{(-1)^{6-j}}{2^j} \prod_{\substack{0 \leq m \leq 6 \\ m \neq j}} \frac{1}{(-1)^{j-m}}
\] \[
p(0) = \sum_{j=0}^{6} \frac{(-1)^{6-j}}{2^j} \prod_{\substack{0 \leq m \leq 6 \\ m \neq j}} (-1)^{m-j} = \sum_{j=0}^{6} \frac{(-1)^{6-j}}{2^j} (-1)^{21-2j} = \sum_{j=0}^{6} \frac{(-1)^{6-j}}{2^j} (-1)^{21} (-1)^{2j} = \sum_{j=0}^{6} \frac{(-1)^{6-j}}{2^j} (-1) \]
